<comment>
The list of values and codes is based on and in compliance with the Medicare Claims Processing Manual Chapter 25 Completing and Processing the Form CMS-1450 Data Set, referencing the Uniform Bill - Form CMS-1450 (UB-04) and the FL 17 - Patient Discharge Status Required. (For all Part A inpatient, SNF, hospice, home health agency (HHA) and outpatient hospital services.) This code indicates the patient's status as of the "Through" date of the billing period (FL 6).
&lt;div style="font-size:2px"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.cms.gov/transmittals/downloads/R1104CP.pdf"&gt;https://www.cms.gov/transmittals/downloads/R1104CP.pdf&lt;/a&gt; Page 35-36
&lt;div style="font-size:3px"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;Codes are available from Medicare contractors and the National Uniform Billing company (NUBC_ (www.nubc.org) via the NUBC's Official UB-04 Data Specifications Manual.
&lt;div style="font-size:3px"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;Contractor site, Knowledge Trek: &lt;a href="http://www.ub04.net/downloads/Medicare_Pub_Ch_25.pdf"&gt;http://www.ub04.net/downloads/Medicare_Pub_Ch_25.pdf&lt;/a&gt; Please reference the section "FL 17 - Patient Status" found on page 23-25 of 126.
</comment>
